<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/471459-i-have-long-been-fascinated-by-the-story">I have long been fascinated by the story of Salim &amp; Anarkali. Is this novel related to that legend?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_471459'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F27298.The_Twentieth_Wife">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/471459-i-have-long-been-fascinated-by-the-story">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/471459-i-have-long-been-fascinated-by-the-story">See all 5 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/41507323-nabilasyifas"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/41507323-nabilasyifas">NabilaSyifaS</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The story of Anarkali was originally written by Indian writer Abdul Halim Shahar, and on the first page of the book he had clearly mentioned it to be <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The story of Anarkali was originally written by Indian writer Abdul Halim Shahar, and on the first page of the book he had clearly mentioned it to be a work of fiction. But the love story of Jahangir and Nur Jahan (Mehrunissa) is true. Hope it helps!<br />Source: Wikipedia and some Indian History Books<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
