<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1367779-azimah-othman"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1217181234i/1367779._UX100_CR0,4,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1367779-azimah-othman">Azimah  Othman</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
Prince Salim and Emperor Jahangir were the same person. It was normal for an Emperor or Sultan to take on another name upon coronation.
</span>
</div>
