  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/49888838" />
    <a title="Jackie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1176067-jackie"><img alt="Jackie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518141143p2/1176067.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/49888838?book_show_action=true">Mar 20, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jackie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jackie" href="/user/show/1176067-jackie">Jackie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1176067-jackie?shelf=2010-read">2010-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer49888838" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3160868030737862398">I first read this book when it came out in 2003. The copy in the library was nice and fresh and just waiting to be cracked open. I fell in love from the first page. Over the years, I still had beautiful images from the book playing in my head. When asked to recommend a book this was usually my top pick. It is now 7 years later and thanks in part to a historical fiction challenge I decided to re-read this book. The same copy from 2003 has now passed many hands. I can tell the book has been loved </span>
  <span id="freeText3160868030737862398" style="display:none">I first read this book when it came out in 2003. The copy in the library was nice and fresh and just waiting to be cracked open. I fell in love from the first page. Over the years, I still had beautiful images from the book playing in my head. When asked to recommend a book this was usually my top pick. It is now 7 years later and thanks in part to a historical fiction challenge I decided to re-read this book. The same copy from 2003 has now passed many hands. I can tell the book has been loved by the many stamps on the due list and stains. I felt nostalgic while re-reading this book and reliving my first experience. The second reading was just as good as the first. The book pretty much as it all- Indian culture, beautiful descriptions, court politics, romance, etc. Oh and who can beat a harem full of beautiful, strong women? </span>
  <a data-text-id="3160868030737862398" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
