<div id="review_1825636487" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1825636487" />
    <a title="Madhuri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/875812-madhuri"><img alt="Madhuri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1449468810p2/875812.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1825636487?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Madhuri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Madhuri" href="/user/show/875812-madhuri">Madhuri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/875812-madhuri?shelf=book-club">book-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1825636487" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10110675373554712660">I found this book a bit superficial, somewhat wrongly masquerading as historical fiction, when it was more a romance. There was little character development or exploration of personal aspirations and ethics. There was some history but it was like a sprinkling of assorted facts with limited perspective. <br/>The protagonist seemed to be a rider of fate rather than a strong willed refugee determined to be an empress as the blurb promises. <br/>Still, despite the misgivings there was something to the story -</span>
  <span id="freeText10110675373554712660" style="display:none">I found this book a bit superficial, somewhat wrongly masquerading as historical fiction, when it was more a romance. There was little character development or exploration of personal aspirations and ethics. There was some history but it was like a sprinkling of assorted facts with limited perspective. <br />The protagonist seemed to be a rider of fate rather than a strong willed refugee determined to be an empress as the blurb promises. <br />Still, despite the misgivings there was something to the story - the treacherous filial relationships, the unsettling quest for power, the politics of zénanas in Mughal sultanate. Not to mention that the drama was a page turner</span>
  <a data-text-id="10110675373554712660" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
